snippet: Japan on Friday gave names to five uninhabited islets in an island group at the center of a territorial dispute with China as part of efforts to reinforce its claim, drawing quick condemnation from Beijing.
abstract: Japan gives names to five uninhabited islets in an island group in East China Sea that are at center of territorial dispute with China as part of efforts to reinforce its claim, drawing quick condemnation from Beijing.
lead_paragraph: Japan on Friday gave names to five uninhabited islets in an island group at the center of a territorial dispute with China as part of efforts to reinforce its claim, drawing quick condemnation from Beijing.
